 {"id":"bd-mblr.5.4.2","title":"Operator runbook with annotated failure traces","description":"Write a detailed runbook for reading E2E logs/artifacts with representative failure trace walkthroughs and root-cause workflow. Output: triage guide tied to schema events.

## Acceptance Criteria
Canonical pass/fail contract is tracked in the issue's structured `acceptance_criteria` field. This section is kept in sync for template conformance and planning hygiene.","design":"Organize by failure class (schema violation, invariant mismatch, nondeterminism, infra fault) with concrete evidence paths.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Runbook contains annotated real failure traces showing how to identify root cause from logs/artifacts. - Runbook maps common failure signatures to first-response diagnostic steps and replay commands. - Runbook remains synchronized with current schema/version and CI artifact layout.  5. Comprehensive unit/property tests with deterministic seeds and invariant checks are required for this bead. 6. At least one deterministic end-to-end scenario script validates integrated behavior with replay instructions and artifact capture. 7. Structured logging/metrics must emit trace/run/scenario identifiers, timing, and actionable failure context, and CI must validate schema conformance.","notes":"Unparented to allow runbook development in parallel; still bound by explicit dependencies and acceptance criteria.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.138699282Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T04:28:33.735991453Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["alien-pass-2026-02-13","ev-gated"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:23:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:23:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
