Canonical pass/fail contract is tracked in the issue's structured `acceptance_criteria` field. This section is kept in sync for template conformance and planning hygiene.","design":"Extend unified logging strategy with a script-specific profile while preserving compatibility with core event schema and artifact conventions.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Script-level structured logging contract is defined and enforceable across all E2E scripts. - Retrofit and conformance tasks are sequenced so CI can fail on schema/quality regressions. - Logs provide machine-triage fields plus human-actionable failure context.  5. Comprehensive unit/property tests with deterministic seeds and invariant checks are required for this bead. 6. At least one deterministic end-to-end scenario script validates integrated behavior with replay instructions and artifact capture. 7. Structured logging/metrics must emit trace/run/scenario identifiers, timing, and actionable failure context, and CI must validate schema conformance.","notes":"Unparented to avoid parent-link deadlock; script-level logging conformance scope and gate semantics unchanged.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:29:15.348378199Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T04:28:34.463178653Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["alien-pass-2026-02-13","ev-gated"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.5","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:23:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
